Python 2.7.6

In a virtualenv, I did this:
pip install rauth
pip install prettytable

Then I grabbed this:
python-yahooapi ( https://github.com/dkempiners/python-yahooapi  )

I had to make these tweaks to that:
diff --git a/yahooapi.py b/yahooapi.py
index 913fdb3..f0c9393 100644
--- a/yahooapi.py
+++ b/yahooapi.py
@@ -40,7 +40,7 @@ class YahooAPI:
                 f = open(tokenfile, "r")
                 self.saved_token = pickle.load(f)
                 f.close()
-            except IOError:
+            except (IOError,EOFError):
                 self.saved_token = None

         if (self.saved_token is not None and
@@ -116,4 +116,4 @@ class YahooAPI:
         if tdiff > self.access_token_lifetime - 60:
             self.refresh_access_token()

-        return self.session.get(request_str)
+        return self.session.get(request_str, params={'format': 'json'})

The keyfile has nothing in it. You need stuff from me (or apply for your own Yahoo key).
The first time you try to run, since there's no token saved, you will be given a URL to follow in a browser.
Once you click "Agree", Yahoo will give you some text.
Paste it at the prompt and you should be good to go from now on.

